**Damage Report:**

**Vehicle Make/Model:** Not specified (based on the image provided)

**Location of Damage:**
- The image shows the rear fender area of the vehicle.
- There appears to be a noticeable dent or indentation on the lower portion of the rear fender near the wheel well.

**Type of Damage:**
- The damage seems to be a dent or impact mark, likely caused by an external force such as a rock, debris, or another vehicle.

**Additional Observations:**
- The dent is located towards the bottom edge of the fender, close to where it meets the wheel well.
- The paint around the dent looks intact, suggesting that the damage may not have been recent or severe enough to cause significant paint damage.
- No other visible damage is apparent in the image.

**Recommendation:**
- Inspect the rest of the vehicle for any additional hidden damage before finalizing the assessment.
- If the dent is confirmed, it may require bodywork to repair the damage properly.

**Conclusion:**
- There is visible damage to the rear fender of the vehicle.
- Further inspection is recommended to ensure all areas are assessed thoroughly.
